{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Brobham | image = | country = England | fullname = unknown | nickname = | birth_date = c.1740 | birth_place = [[England]] | batting = unknown hand | bowling = underarm: unknown hand and type | role = batsman | club1 = unknown | year1 = c.1761–1775 | club2 = | year2 = | date = 19 March | year = 2013 | columns = 0 | source = [[G. B. Buckley]] }}
'''Brobham''' (first name and dates unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket|first-class]] [[cricket]]er who was active in the 1760s and 1770s. He played for [[Dartford Cricket Club|Dartford]] and [[Kent county cricket teams|Kent]]. Brobham was recorded twice. He played for [[John Frederick Sackville, 3rd Duke of Dorset]]'s team in a [[single wicket cricket|single wicket "fives" match]] at the [[Artillery Ground]] in May 1768.<ref>Buckley, p.47.</ref> In September 1775, he was a member of the Dartford team playing against [[Chertsey Cricket Club|Chertsey]] at [[Laleham Burway]].<ref>Buckley, p.75.</ref>
As Brobham had established his reputation by 1768, he must have been active for some years previously and was possibly near the end of his career in 1775. Very few players were mentioned by name in contemporary reports and there are no other references to Brobham.
