{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Castrén | nickname = | image = [[File:AC Oulu vs FC Honka in Oulu 20070722 02.JPG|250px|alt=AC Oulu vs FC Honka football game in the stadium in the summer 2007.]] | fullname = | location = [[Oulu]], [[Finland]] | coordinates = {{coord|65|01|49|N|25|29|42|E|type:landmark_region:FI-OL}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = City of [[Oulu]] | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 4 000 | dimensions = 110 × 78 m<ref name="ouka2013">{{cite web | url = http://www.ouka.fi/oulu/liikunta-ja-ulkoilu/castrenin-urheilukeskus | title = Castrenin urheilukeskus | publisher = City of Oulu | year = 2013 | accessdate = July 25, 2013}}</ref> }}
'''Castrén''' is a football [[stadium]] in the [[Välivainio]] neighbourhood of [[Oulu]], [[Finland]]. The stadium holds 4 000 spectators. It is the home ground of sports clubs [[Oulun Luistinseura]], [[JS Hercules]] and [[Oulun Palloseura]].
