{{More footnotes|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox gymnast | name = Evmorfia Dona | gender = w | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = | altname = | nickname = | country = {{flagu|Greece}} | regions = | formercountry = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|8|23|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Grevena]], Greece | hometown = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | height = 5-5.5 (167 cm) | weight = 97 lbs (44 kg) | discipline = RG | level = Senior International Elite | natlteam = 1999–2007 (?) | club = FO Proteas Grev. | gym = | collegeteam = | headcoach = | assistcoach = | formercoach = | choreographer = | music = | eponymousskills = | retired = | worldranking = | updated = | show-medals = yes | medaltemplates = <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCompetition | [[European Team Gymnastics Championships|European Team Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze|[[1999 European Gymnastics Masters|1999 Patras]]|Team}} }}
''' Evmorfia Dona''' (also written as '''Evmorfia Ntona''', Ευμορφία Ντώνα; born 23 August 1984 in [[Grevena]]) was a Greek individual and group [[rhythmic gymnast]]. She represents her nation at international competitions.
She participated at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in Sydney. She also competed at world championships, including at the 1999, 2005 and [[2007 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |title=28th RHYTHMIC GYMNASTICS WORLD CHAMPIONSHIPS: Patras (GRE) September 16th – 23rd 2007 |quote=DONA Evmorfia |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000006030100FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF01 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509162626/http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000006030100FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF01 |archive-date=9 May 2016 |publisher=LonginesTiming.com |date=16 September 2007 |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ev/dona-evmorfia-1.html |title=Dona Evmorfia |accessdate=17 June 2016}}</ref>
