{{Infobox WTCC race | Name = FIA WTCC Race of Russia | Flag = Flag of Russia.svg | Circuit = [[Moscow Raceway]] | Circuit_image = Moscow Raceway FIM.svg | Times_held = 4 | First_held = 2013 | Last_held = 2016 | Most_wins_driver = {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Yvan Muller]] (2) | Most_wins_constructor = {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Citroën]] (3) | Current_year = 2016 | Race_1_winner = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Gabriele Tarquini]] | Race_1_winning_team = ([[Lada Sport|Lada Sport Rosneft]]) | Race_2_winner = {{flagicon|NED}} [[Nick Catsburg]] | Race_2_winning_team = ([[Lada Sport|Lada Sport Rosneft]]) }}
The '''FIA WTCC Race of Russia''' is a round of the [[World Touring Car Championship]], which was held for the first time in [[2013 World Touring Car Championship season|2013]] at the [[Moscow Raceway]] in [[Volokolamsk]], {{convert|70|km|mi}} from the capital, [[Moscow]].<ref name="final calendar">{{cite news|title=WTCC to pay first visit to Russia in 2013 |url=http://www.fiawtcc.com/news/detail/id/573 |work=fiawtcc.com |publisher=[[World Touring Car Championship]] |date=21 December 2012 |accessdate=22 January 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020054144/http://www.fiawtcc.com/news/detail/id/573 |archivedate=20 October 2013 |df= }}</ref>
