==Britain== The [[British GAA|British Provincial Board]] is responsible for seven areas of Britain that are treated as "counties" by the GAA. Their representative teams naturally have standard kit colours like the Irish counties. {| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;" |- bgcolor="#efefef" ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|County!!width="250"|Description |- | [[File:Colours of Leitrim.svg|100px|border]] || [[Gloucestershire GAA|Gloucestershire]] || Gold and Green |- | [[File:Colours of Leitrim.svg|100px|border]] || [[Hertfordshire GAA|Hertfordshire]] || Green and Yellow |- | [[File:Colours of Roscommon.svg|100px|border]] || [[Lancashire GAA|Lancashire]] || Blue and Yellow |- | [[File:Colours of Limerick.svg|100px|border]] || [[London GAA|London]] || Green and White |- | || [[Scotland GAA|Scotland]] || |- | [[File:Colours of Sligo.svg|100px|border]] || [[Warwickshire GAA|Warwickshire]] || Black and White |- | [[File:Colours of Laois.svg|100px|border]]|| [[Yorkshire GAA|Yorkshire]] || Blue and White |}
